01:01:02.075 --> 01:01:04.912
- 19.83.
- Okay.

695
01:01:08.415 --> 01:01:10.542
Are you here all by yourself?

696
01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:16.173
Ma'am. I'm 8 years old.
You think I would be here alone?

697
01:01:16.256 --> 01:01:18.592
I don't think so.

698
01:01:18.717 --> 01:01:20.969
- Where's your mom?
- My mom's in the car.

699
01:01:21.095 --> 01:01:23.472
<i>- And where is your father?
- He's at work.</i>

700
01:01:23.597 --> 01:01:26.350
- What about your brothers and your sisters?
- I'm an only child.

701
01:01:26.433 --> 01:01:28.936
- Where do you live?
- I can't tell you that.

702
01:01:29.061 --> 01:01:32.064
- Why not?
- 'Cause you're a stranger.

703
01:02:10.644 --> 01:02:14.439
Hello. Kevin!

704
01:02:17.275 --> 01:02:20.653
<i>Shut up.</i>

705
01:02:32.332 --> 01:02:34.209
I don't get it.

706
01:02:34.334 --> 01:02:37.004
I mean. right now it looks
like there's nobody home.

707
01:02:37.129 --> 01:02:40.674
Last night the place is jumpin'.

708
01:02:40.799 --> 01:02:44.511
Somethin' ain't right.
Go check it out.

709
01:02:53.103 --> 01:02:55.022
Now?

710
01:02:55.147 --> 01:02:57.024
No. tomorrow. egghead. Now!

711
01:02:57.149 --> 01:02:59.776
<i>Go ahead!</i>

712
01:02:59.860 --> 01:03:02.070
"Now?"

713
01:03:19.079 --> 01:03:21.457
<i>Shit.</i>

714
01:03:23.592 --> 01:03:26.512
- Get the hell outta here.
- All right. Johnny.

715
01:03:26.595 --> 01:03:29.723
<i>- But what about my money?
- What money?</i>

716
01:03:29.848 --> 01:03:32.518
<i>Acey said you had
some dough for me.</i>

717
01:03:32.643 --> 01:03:37.523
<i>- Is that a fact? How much do I owe you?
- Acey said 10%.</i>

718
01:03:37.606 --> 01:03:42.611
<i>- Too bad Acey ain't in charge no more.
- What do you mean?</i>

719
01:03:42.736 --> 01:03:46.114
<i>He's upstairs taking a bath.</i>

720
01:03:46.240 --> 01:03:48.909
<i>He'll call you when he gets out.</i>

721
01:03:49.034 --> 01:03:50.911
<i>Hey.</i>

722
01:03:51.036 --> 01:03:54.039
<i>I tell you what
I'm gonna give you. Snakes.</i>

723
01:03:54.122 --> 01:03:57.960
<i>- Snakes?
- I'm gonna give you to the count of 10...</i>

724
01:03:58.085 --> 01:04:00.379
<i>to get your ugly. yellow...</i>

725
01:04:00.462 --> 01:04:04.925
no-good keister off my property
before I pump your guts full of lead.

726
01:04:05.008 --> 01:04:07.719
<i>All right. Johnny. I'm sorry.
I'm goin'.</i>

727
01:04:07.803 --> 01:04:10.764
<i>1. 2. 10!</i>

728
01:04:29.992 --> 01:04:33.162
<i>Keep the change.
ya filthy animal.</i>

729
01:04:37.166 --> 01:04:38.242
What happened?

730
01:04:38.268 --> 01:04:41.770
I don't know who's in there. but
somebody just got blown away!

731
01:04:41.855 --> 01:04:43.856
Somebody beat us to the job.
They're in there!

732
01:04:44.256 --> 01:04:48.260
Two of' em. They was arguing.
One of' em blew the other one away.

733
01:04:48.343 --> 01:04:50.053
- Who?
- I don't know.

734
01:04:50.137 --> 01:04:52.598
<i>I thought I recognized
one of their voices.</i>

735
01:04:52.681 --> 01:04:55.893
And I know I heard that name
Snakes before.

736
01:04:55.976 --> 01:04:58.479
Snakes? Snakes. Snakes.

737
01:04:58.604 --> 01:05:00.689
- I don't know no Snakes.
<i>- Snakes.</i>

738
01:05:00.814 --> 01:05:03.358
Let's get out of here.

739
01:05:05.777 --> 01:05:08.447
Hold it. hold it.
Let's wait and see who it is.

740
01:05:08.530 --> 01:05:10.449
We work this neighborhood too.

741
01:05:10.532 --> 01:05:13.327
<i>- Yeah.
- Supposin' the cops finger us for a job...</i>

742
01:05:13.452 --> 01:05:16.455
and they start asking us questions
about a murder in the area.

743
01:05:16.538 --> 01:05:19.666
Wouldn't it be nice to have
a face to go with their questions?

744
01:05:21.543 --> 01:05:23.504
That's a good idea.

745
01:05:23.629 --> 01:05:27.049
Of course it's a good idea.
Snakes?

746
01:05:27.174 --> 01:05:30.052
He sounded like a snake.

747
01:05:40.176 --> 01:05:42.176
Dad?

748
01:05:43.200 --> 01:05:45.200
Linnie what are you doing up. sweet heart?

749
01:05:46.024 --> 01:05:48.024
Have you heard from Kevin?

750
01:05:48.348 --> 01:05:50.348
No.

751
01:05:50.372 --> 01:05:52.372
You wanna sit down?

752
01:05:58.896 --> 01:06:00.896
Where's mom?

753
01:06:02.120 --> 01:06:05.520
I think she ran off with
some Parisian Playboy.

754
01:06:06.244 --> 01:06:08.244
Dad.

755
01:06:08.268 --> 01:06:12.268
She just got on to a plane to
Scranton. to go back and get Kevin.

756
01:06:14.192 --> 01:06:18.192
She won't be here from Christmas.
Kevin won't be here for Christmas.

757
01:06:18.516 --> 01:06:20.516
It won't even be like Christmas.

758
01:06:21.540 --> 01:06:23.540
Well let's postpone Christmas a day.

759
01:06:23.564 --> 01:06:25.564
I think that's a bad idea.

760
01:06:25.588 --> 01:06:27.588
We don't have much choice. sweetheart.

761
01:06:29.112 --> 01:06:31.312
Family shouldn't be apart on Christmas.

762
01:06:31.836 --> 01:06:35.836
No matter how mean they are to
each other the rest of the year.

763
01:06:35.860 --> 01:06:39.260
Us here. them there.
It's stupid dad.

764
01:06:39.584 --> 01:06:41.584
Christmas isn't about Paris.

765
01:06:42.808 --> 01:06:44.808
What is Christmas about?

766
01:06:46.232 --> 01:06:48.232
Christmas is about...

767
01:06:48.556 --> 01:06:50.556
Families. Being together.

768
01:06:53.080 --> 01:06:55.080
Atta girl...

769
01:07:03.311 --> 01:07:04.798
Everything's full.

770
01:07:04.854 --> 01:07:06.731
Everything's full?

771
01:07:06.856 --> 01:07:09.066
I'm very sorry.
but it is Christmas Eve.

772
01:07:09.191 --> 01:07:11.319
What about another airline?

773
01:07:16.741 --> 01:07:19.702
Nothing available.
May I help you get a hotel room in the city?

774
01:07:19.827 --> 01:07:22.121
<i>Tomorrow afternoon we can
get you a flight to Chicago.</i>

775
01:07:22.147 --> 01:07:23.356
I can't wait that long.

776
01:07:23.414 --> 01:07:27.835
I'm terribly sorry. ma'am. but we're
doing absolutely everything we can.

777
01:07:32.006 --> 01:07:35.134
Go ahead. I'm in your way.
You have places to go. people to see.

778
01:07:35.217 --> 01:07:38.554
You got a ticket there.
That's good. Excuse me. Look.

779
01:07:38.679 --> 01:07:42.683
<i>I have been awake for almost 60 hours.
I'm tired and I'm dirty.</i>

780
01:07:42.767 --> 01:07:47.229
I have been from Chicago to Paris
to Dallas to--Where the hell am I?

781
01:07:47.355 --> 01:07:49.357
Scranton.

782
01:07:49.440 --> 01:07:52.109
I am trying to get home
to my 8-year-old son!

783
01:07:52.234 --> 01:07:55.613
And now that I'm this close.
you're telling me it's hopeless?

784
01:07:55.738 --> 01:07:59.367
- I'm sorry.
- No. No. no. no. no way. This is Christmas!

785
01:07:59.450 --> 01:08:01.369
The season of perpetual hope!

786
01:08:01.452 --> 01:08:02.243
<i>Ma'am. if I--</i>

787
01:08:02.269 --> 01:08:05.272
<i>If I have to get out on
your runway and hitchhike...</i>

788
01:08:05.373 --> 01:08:07.291
if it costs me everything I own...

789
01:08:07.416 --> 01:08:10.252
if I have to sell my soul
to the devil himself...

790
01:08:10.378 --> 01:08:13.547
I am going to get home
to my son.

791
01:08:13.631 --> 01:08:16.934
<i>Ma'am. if there was anything at
all I could do for you today--</i>

792
01:08:16.960 --> 01:08:17.785
Do it.

793
01:08:17.885 --> 01:08:20.471
<i>- Do anything.
- I can get you a hotel room.</i>

794
01:08:20.596 --> 01:08:23.015
- What?
- Excuse me.

795
01:08:23.099 --> 01:08:28.813
<i>Can you excuse us for a second? Can I see you
for a second? Please. Excuse us. Come.</i>

796
01:08:28.938 --> 01:08:32.108
Couldn't help but hearin'
you got a little bit of a dilemma there.

797
01:08:32.233 --> 01:08:34.819
We got a crisis ourselves.

798
01:08:34.944 --> 01:08:38.364
Allow me to introduce myself.
Gus Polinski. How are you?

799
01:08:38.489 --> 01:08:41.909
Polka king of the Midwest?

800
01:08:44.787 --> 01:08:47.540
The Kenosha Kickers?

801
01:08:47.623 --> 01:08:49.291
- Hi there.
- Hiya.

802
01:08:49.417 --> 01:08:52.253
No? That's okay. I thought
you might've recognized--

803
01:08:52.336 --> 01:08:55.297
Anyways. uh. I had
a few hits a few years ago.

804
01:08:55.381 --> 01:08:58.676
Uh. that's why. you know--
"Polka. Polka. Polka"?

805
01:09:01.262 --> 01:09:03.264
No? "Twin Lakes Polka."

806
01:09:03.347 --> 01:09:06.809
"Yamahoozie Polka. "
a.k.a. "Kiss Me Polka."

807
01:09:06.934 --> 01:09:09.562
- "Polka Twist."
- These are songs?

808
01:09:09.645 --> 01:09:13.065
Yeah. Yeah. We--
Some fairly big hits for us.

809
01:09:13.149 --> 01:09:15.776
- You know. in the early '70s. you know?
- Oh.

810
01:09:15.860 --> 01:09:18.487
Yeah. we sold
about 623 copies of that.

811
01:09:18.612 --> 01:09:21.240
- In Chicago?
- No. Sheboygan. Very big in Sheboygan.

812
01:09:21.324 --> 01:09:23.492
I'm sorry. Did you say
you could help me?

813
01:09:23.617 --> 01:09:25.745
Anyway. I'm rambling on here.

814
01:09:25.828 --> 01:09:28.914
<i>Our flight was canceled.
so we gotta drive.</i>

815
01:09:28.998 --> 01:09:32.585
So. uh. see the guy in the yellow jacket
over there by the Budget sign?

816
01:09:32.668 --> 01:09:36.422
<i>He's gonna rent us a nice big. uh. van.
and we're gonna drive to Milwaukee.</i>

817
01:09:36.505 --> 01:09:40.801
I heard you had some problems here. uh. gettin'
to Chicago to see your kid or somethin'?

818
01:09:40.926 --> 01:09:45.014
Uh. my son. He--
We left and he's there.

819
01:09:45.139 --> 01:09:49.226
<i>Aw. geez. If you have to get
to Chicago. we'll gladly drive you.</i>

820
01:09:49.352 --> 01:09:51.604
It's on the way to Milwaukee.

821
01:09:51.687 --> 01:09:54.315
<i>- You'd give me a ride?
- Sure we will. Why not. you know?</i>

822
01:09:54.440 --> 01:09:56.984
<i>- You gotta get home and see your kid.
- A ride to Chicago?</i>

823
01:09:57.068 --> 01:09:58.944
Sure. You know.
it's Christmas time.

824
01:09:59.028 --> 01:10:01.572
Thank you.
Oh. thank you.

825
01:10:01.697 --> 01:10:03.991
If you don't mind goin'
with some polka bums.

826
01:10:04.075 --> 01:10:05.993
No. I'd love to.

827
01:10:27.723 --> 01:10:30.601
- Hey. Marv. Marv. Marv.
- What?

828
01:10:30.726 --> 01:10:33.187
Look at this.

829
01:10:37.733 --> 01:10:42.113
I think we're gettin' scammed
by a "kindygartener."

830
01:11:12.226 --> 01:11:14.770
Dad. can you come here
and help me?

831
01:11:19.275 --> 01:11:23.529
Remember that kid we saw
the other day? He lives here.

832
01:11:23.612 --> 01:11:26.532
Well. if the kid's there.
the parents gotta be.

833
01:11:26.615 --> 01:11:29.201
He's home alone.

834
01:11:37.084 --> 01:11:39.420
You gotta be kiddin'.
You wanna come back tonight?

835
01:11:39.503 --> 01:11:41.422
- Uh-huh.
- Even with the kid here?

836
01:11:41.505 --> 01:11:43.632
- Uh-huh.
- I don't think that's a good idea.

837
01:11:43.758 --> 01:11:47.219
That house is the only reason we started
workin' this block in the first place.

838
01:11:47.303 --> 01:11:50.014
Ever since I laid eyes
on that house. I wanted it.

839
01:11:50.139 --> 01:11:52.475
<i>So let's take it
one step at a time. okay?</i>

840
01:11:52.600 --> 01:11:56.062
We'll unload the van. We'll get a bite
to eat. We'll come back about 9:00.

841
01:11:56.187 --> 01:11:59.106
<i>- 9:00.
- This way it's dark then.</i>

842
01:11:59.190 --> 01:12:02.318
Yeah. Kids are scared
of the dark.

843
01:12:02.443 --> 01:12:05.279
You're afraid of the dark too. Marv.
You know you are.

844
01:12:05.363 --> 01:12:08.074
No. I'm not!

845
01:12:08.157 --> 01:12:10.660
- Yes. you are.
- I'm not. not. not.

846
01:12:10.785 --> 01:12:14.997
<i>- You are so.
- Mom. where are you?</i>

847
01:12:28.386 --> 01:12:30.304
Do you play?

848
01:12:30.388 --> 01:12:32.473
You want to try it?
Go ahead. Try it.

849
01:12:32.556 --> 01:12:34.809
- Try it. Try it.
- No.

850
01:12:34.934 --> 01:12:36.978
Okay.

851
01:13:01.210 --> 01:13:04.630
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

852
01:13:04.755 --> 01:13:08.718
<i>- Hey. nice shoes.
- Oh. thanks.</i>

853
01:13:08.843 --> 01:13:12.471
Is he still here? It's really important
that I see him.

854
01:13:12.555 --> 01:13:17.852
He's getting in his car. I guess
if you hurry. you can catch him.

855
01:13:17.935 --> 01:13:22.398
Damn! How low can you get? Givin' Kris Kringle
a parking ticket on Christmas Eve.

856
01:13:22.523 --> 01:13:25.609
What's next?
Rabies shots for the Easter Bunny?

857
01:13:25.735 --> 01:13:28.321
Santa. hold on!

858
01:13:28.404 --> 01:13:30.531
Can I talk to you for a minute?

859
01:13:30.614 --> 01:13:33.617
If you make it quick. Santa's got
a little get-together he's late for.

860
01:13:33.743 --> 01:13:35.619
Okay. I know you're not
the real Santa Claus.

861
01:13:35.745 --> 01:13:39.623
What makes you say that?
Just out of curiosity.

862
01:13:39.749 --> 01:13:42.376
I'm old enough
to know how it works.

863
01:13:42.460 --> 01:13:45.546
<i>- All right.
- But I also know that you work for him.</i>

864
01:13:45.629 --> 01:13:48.674
<i>- And I'd like you to give him a message.
- Shoot.</i>

865
01:13:48.758 --> 01:13:52.887
I'm Kevin McCallister.
671 Lincoln Boulevard.

866
01:13:52.970 --> 01:13:55.640
- Do you need the phone number?
- No. that's all right.

867
01:13:55.765 --> 01:13:57.933
Okay.
This is extremely important.

868
01:13:58.059 --> 01:14:02.855
Would you please tell him that. instead of
presents this year. I just want my family back.

869
01:14:02.938 --> 01:14:07.860
<i>No toys. Nothing but Peter.
Kate. Buzz. Megan. Linnie and Jeff.</i>

870
01:14:07.943 --> 01:14:10.154
And my aunt and my cousins.

871
01:14:10.279 --> 01:14:13.449
And. if he has time.
my Uncle Frank. Okay?

872
01:14:15.159 --> 01:14:18.329
Okay. I'll see what I can do.

873
01:14:18.454 --> 01:14:21.374
- Thanks.
- Wait. Hold on a second.

874
01:14:21.457 --> 01:14:24.585
My elf took the last of the candy canes
home to her boyfriend.

875
01:14:24.710 --> 01:14:26.754
- That's okay.
- No. no. no. Don't be silly.

876
01:14:26.837 --> 01:14:29.840
Everybody who sees Santa
has gotta get... somethin'.

877
01:14:29.965 --> 01:14:32.134
Here. Hold out
your little paw there.

878
01:14:32.259 --> 01:14:35.346
There you go.
Don't spoil your dinner.

879
01:14:35.471 --> 01:14:38.057
I won't. Thanks.

880
01:14:48.985 --> 01:14:51.529
Son of a--

881
01:17:47.705 --> 01:17:49.957
Merry Christmas.

882
01:17:50.041 --> 01:17:51.500
Huh?

883
01:17:51.625 --> 01:17:53.669
May I sit down?

884
01:18:04.138 --> 01:18:08.643
That's my granddaughter up there.
The little red-haired girl.

885
01:18:10.853 --> 01:18:12.521
She's about your age.

886
01:18:12.647 --> 01:18:14.857
- Do you know her?
- No.

887
01:18:14.982 --> 01:18:18.027
- You live next to me. don't you?
- Yeah.

888
01:18:18.152 --> 01:18:22.615
You can say hello when you see me.
You don't have to be afraid.

889
01:18:22.698 --> 01:18:26.619
There's a lot of things going around
about me. but none of it's true.

890
01:18:26.702 --> 01:18:28.621
Okay?

891
01:18:28.704 --> 01:18:30.915
- You been a good boy this year?
- I think so.

892
01:18:31.040 --> 01:18:33.125
<i>Swear to it?</i>

893
01:18:33.209 --> 01:18:35.920
- No.
- Yeah. I had a feeling.

894
01:18:36.045 --> 01:18:39.173
Well. this is the place to be
if you're feeling bad about yourself.

895
01:18:39.256 --> 01:18:42.176
<i>- It is?
- I think so.</i>

896
01:18:42.259 --> 01:18:44.971
<i>- Are you feeling bad about yourself?.
- No.</i>

897
01:18:49.225 --> 01:18:51.477
I've been kind of a pain lately.

898
01:18:51.560 --> 01:18:53.980
<i>I said some things
I shouldn't have.</i>

899
01:18:54.063 --> 01:18:57.358
I really haven't been
too good this year.

900
01:18:57.441 --> 01:19:00.277
<i>- Yeah.
- I'm kind of upset about it...</i>

901
01:19:00.403 --> 01:19:02.530
because I really like my family.

902
01:19:02.655 --> 01:19:05.157
Even though sometimes
I say I don't.

903
01:19:05.282 --> 01:19:08.703
Sometimes I even think I don't.
Do you get that?

904
01:19:08.786 --> 01:19:13.290
I think so. How you feel about
your family is a complicated thing.

905
01:19:13.416 --> 01:19:16.877
Especially with an older brother.

906
01:19:17.003 --> 01:19:21.257
<i>Deep down you always love 'em.
but you can forget that you love 'em.</i>

907
01:19:21.382 --> 01:19:24.051
And you can hurt them.
and they can hurt you.

908
01:19:24.176 --> 01:19:27.888
And that's not just
because you're young.

909
01:19:28.014 --> 01:19:31.225
You want to know the real reason
that I'm here right now?

910
01:19:31.350 --> 01:19:33.269
Sure.

911
01:19:33.352 --> 01:19:36.981
I came to hear my granddaughter sing.
and I can't come and hear her tonight.

912
01:19:37.106 --> 01:19:42.737
- You have plans?
- No. I'm not welcome.

913
01:19:42.820 --> 01:19:46.657
- At church?
- Oh. you're always welcome at church.

914
01:19:46.782 --> 01:19:49.160
I'm not welcome with my son.

915
01:19:49.285 --> 01:19:53.956
<i>Years back. before you and
your family moved on the block...</i>

916
01:19:54.081 --> 01:19:56.542
I had an argument with my son.

917
01:19:56.667 --> 01:20:00.921
- How old is he?
- Oh. he's grown up.

918
01:20:01.005 --> 01:20:03.632
We lost our tempers...

919
01:20:03.758 --> 01:20:06.719
and I said I didn't care
to see him anymore.

920
01:20:06.802 --> 01:20:11.724
He said the same. and we haven't
spoken to each other since.

921
01:20:11.807 --> 01:20:14.644
If you miss him.
why don't you call him?

922
01:20:14.769 --> 01:20:17.438
I'm afraid if I call him.
he won't talk to me.

923
01:20:17.563 --> 01:20:19.774
<i>How do you know?</i>

924
01:20:19.857 --> 01:20:22.860
I don't know.
I'm just afraid he won't.

925
01:20:22.985 --> 01:20:26.656
No offense. but aren't you
a little old to be afraid?

926
01:20:26.781 --> 01:20:30.284
You can be a little old
for a lot of things.

927
01:20:30.409 --> 01:20:32.620
You're never too old
to be afraid.

928
01:20:32.745 --> 01:20:35.498
That's true. I've always
been afraid of our basement.

929
01:20:35.623 --> 01:20:39.043
It's dark. there's weird stuff
down there. and it smells funny.

930
01:20:39.168 --> 01:20:42.546
That sort of thing.
It's bothered me for years.

931
01:20:42.672 --> 01:20:45.091
Basements are like that.

932
01:20:45.174 --> 01:20:48.094
Then I made myself go down there
to do some laundry...

933
01:20:48.177 --> 01:20:50.179
and I found out
it's not so bad.

934
01:20:50.262 --> 01:20:52.556
All this time
I've been worrying about it...

935
01:20:52.682 --> 01:20:54.934
but if you turn on the lights.
it's no big deal.

936
01:20:55.017 --> 01:20:59.480
- What's your point?
- My point is you should call your son.

937
01:20:59.563 --> 01:21:01.649
What if he won't talk to me?

938
01:21:01.732 --> 01:21:05.069
At least you'll know.
Then you could stop worrying about it...

939
01:21:05.194 --> 01:21:07.780
<i>and you won't have to be
afraid anymore.</i>

940
01:21:07.863 --> 01:21:11.450
I don't care how mad I was.
I'd talk to my dad...

941
01:21:11.534 --> 01:21:13.452
especially around the holidays.

942
01:21:13.536 --> 01:21:16.664
I don't know.

943
01:21:16.789 --> 01:21:19.959
<i>Just give it a shot.
For your granddaughter anyway.</i>

944
01:21:20.042 --> 01:21:23.421
I'm sure she misses you...
and the presents.

945
01:21:23.546 --> 01:21:25.381
I send her a check.

946
01:21:25.506 --> 01:21:29.802
I wish my grandparents sent that.
They always send me clothes.

947
01:21:29.885 --> 01:21:32.805
Last year I got a sweater
with a big bird knitted on it.

948
01:21:32.888 --> 01:21:36.183
- Oh. that's nice.
- Not for a guy in the second grade.

949
01:21:36.267 --> 01:21:39.228
You can get beat up
for wearing something like that.

950
01:21:39.353 --> 01:21:41.480
- Oh?
- Yeah.

951
01:21:41.564 --> 01:21:45.693
I have a friend who got nailed 'cause there
was a rumor he wore dinosaur pajamas.

952
01:21:45.776 --> 01:21:49.071
You'd better run along home
where you belong.

953
01:21:49.196 --> 01:21:51.073
You think about what I said.

954
01:21:51.198 --> 01:21:52.950
<i>- All right?
- Okay.</i>

955
01:21:53.075 --> 01:21:56.954
- It was nice talking to you.
- Nice talking to you.

956
01:22:02.877 --> 01:22:06.172
- What about you?
- Me?

957
01:22:06.255 --> 01:22:08.257
Yeah. You and your son.

958
01:22:08.382 --> 01:22:11.677
We'll see what happens.

959
01:22:11.761 --> 01:22:14.722
Merry Christmas.

960
01:22:14.805 --> 01:22:16.724
Merry Christmas.

961
01:23:09.485 --> 01:23:13.489
This is my house.
I have to defend it.

962
01:24:41.077 --> 01:24:44.955
Okay. we'll check it out first.
We can always come back for the truck.

963
01:24:51.587 --> 01:24:53.839
How do you wanna go in?

964
01:24:53.923 --> 01:24:57.385
We'll go to the back door.
Maybe he'll let us in. You never know.

965
01:24:57.468 --> 01:25:00.930
Yeah. He's a kid.
Kids are stupid.

966
01:25:02.974 --> 01:25:06.894
Bless this highly nutritious microwavable
macaroni and cheese dinner...

967
01:25:06.978 --> 01:25:09.021
and the people
who sold it on sale.

968
01:25:09.105 --> 01:25:11.023
Amen.

969
01:25:34.880 --> 01:25:37.758
This is it.
Don't get scared now.

970
01:25:51.063 --> 01:25:53.524
<i>Merry Christmas. little fella.</i>

971
01:25:53.649 --> 01:25:56.193
We know that you're in there...

972
01:25:56.319 --> 01:25:59.196
and that you're all alone.

973
01:25:59.322 --> 01:26:01.949
Yeah. come on. kid. Open up.

974
01:26:02.033 --> 01:26:05.578
It's Santa Claus and his elf.

975
01:26:06.996 --> 01:26:09.248
We're not gonna hurt you.

976
01:26:09.332 --> 01:26:13.294
No. no. We got
some nice presents for you.

977
01:26:13.377 --> 01:26:16.839
<i>Be a good little fella now
and open the door.</i>

978
01:26:19.759 --> 01:26:22.511
Shoot!

979
01:26:22.636 --> 01:26:26.390
What? What? What?

980
01:26:26.515 --> 01:26:29.518
What? What happened?

981
01:26:29.644 --> 01:26:33.189
Get that little--

982
01:26:42.531 --> 01:26:44.700
Hello.

983
01:26:50.039 --> 01:26:52.500
Yes! Yes!

984
01:26:52.583 --> 01:26:54.669
The little jerk is armed!

985
01:26:54.752 --> 01:26:58.673
That's it! That's it! I'm goin' around
the front! You go down the basement!

986
01:26:58.756 --> 01:27:01.217
That little--

987
01:27:37.503 --> 01:27:39.547
Ow!

988
01:28:01.193 --> 01:28:03.404
That smart aleck.

989
01:29:31.158 --> 01:29:36.080
Oh. boy. that's it. you little--
you little son of a--

990
01:29:36.205 --> 01:29:39.166
Oh. not this time.
you little brat.

991
01:29:42.753 --> 01:29:45.214
You little creep. you.
where are you?

992
01:29:45.339 --> 01:29:49.510
Where are you. you little creep?

993
01:30:09.238 --> 01:30:13.159
Yes! Yes!
Yes. yes. yes. yes!

994
01:30:43.898 --> 01:30:46.692
I'll rip his head off!

995
01:30:52.948 --> 01:30:57.662
You're dead. kid.

996
01:31:44.709 --> 01:31:47.837
Where are you.
you little creep?

997
01:32:03.185 --> 01:32:06.814
<i>Harry! I'm comin' in!</i>

998
01:32:11.444 --> 01:32:13.821
<i>Oh. no. I'm really scared!</i>

999
01:32:13.946 --> 01:32:16.574
It's too late for you. kid.
We're already in the house.

1000
01:32:16.699 --> 01:32:20.745
<i>- We're gonna get you!
- Okay. Come and get me.</i>

1001
01:32:20.870 --> 01:32:23.414
Why. you--

1002
01:32:27.877 --> 01:32:30.338
Now you're dead!

1003
01:32:54.612 --> 01:32:57.114
I'm gonna kill that kid!

1004
01:33:11.587 --> 01:33:14.632
- Marv!
- Harry?

1005
01:33:14.757 --> 01:33:16.759
Why the hell did
you take your shoes off?

1006
01:33:16.884 --> 01:33:20.012
Why the hell are you
dressed like a chicken?

1007
01:33:21.430 --> 01:33:25.184
I'm up here. you morons!
Come and get me!

1008
01:33:27.395 --> 01:33:31.065
You guys give up.
or are you thirsty for more?

1009
01:33:40.783 --> 01:33:43.244
<i>- Heads up!
- Huh?</i>

1010
01:33:43.327 --> 01:33:46.497
Don't worry. Marv. I'll get him for you.

1011
01:33:46.622 --> 01:33:50.126
Ow!

1012
01:33:50.251 --> 01:33:53.629
Yes!

1013
01:33:57.800 --> 01:34:00.511
He's only a kid. Harry.
We can take him.

1014
01:34:00.636 --> 01:34:02.596
- Aw. shut up. will ya!
- Oh!

1015
01:34:02.722 --> 01:34:05.725
- What is it?
- You're missin' some teeth.

1016
01:34:05.808 --> 01:34:10.021
Where? It's my gold tooth.
My gold tooth! I'll kill him!

1017
01:34:10.146 --> 01:34:13.524
I'll kill him!

1018
01:34:13.649 --> 01:34:16.444
You bomb me
with one more can. kid...

1019
01:34:16.527 --> 01:34:20.698
and I'll snap off your cojones
and boil them in motor oil!

1020
01:34:23.159 --> 01:34:25.286
<i>911 Emergency.</i>

1021
01:34:25.369 --> 01:34:28.122
Help. My house is being robbed.

1022
01:34:28.205 --> 01:34:32.793
My address is 656 Lincoln Boulevard.
My name's Murphy.

1023
01:34:35.504 --> 01:34:38.049
Watch it. You never know
what's up there.

1024
01:34:38.174 --> 01:34:41.052
There he is!

1025
01:34:42.178 --> 01:34:45.306
Ah! I got ya!

1026
01:34:45.389 --> 01:34:48.768
I got him. Harry!
Harry. I got him!

1027
01:34:48.851 --> 01:34:51.937
<i>Harry. get up! Give me a hand!</i>

1028
01:34:52.021 --> 01:34:56.192
<i>Ow! I got him!</i>

1029
01:34:56.317 --> 01:34:59.779
Harry. help me! Get up!

1030
01:34:59.904 --> 01:35:02.657
<i>I got him!</i>

1031
01:35:41.195 --> 01:35:46.033
- What are you doing. Marv?
- Harry. don't move.

1032
01:35:46.117 --> 01:35:50.079
- Marv?
- Don't... move!

1033
01:35:50.204 --> 01:35:53.499
<i>Marv. what are you doing?
Marv--</i>

1034
01:35:56.585 --> 01:36:00.172
Did I get him?
Did I get him?

1035
01:36:00.256 --> 01:36:02.591
Where is it?
Where is it?

1036
01:36:02.717 --> 01:36:05.886
Never mind did you get it!
How do you like it? Huh?

1037
01:36:05.970 --> 01:36:09.765
You jerk! Get that kid!
Go on! Get the kid!

1038
01:36:13.144 --> 01:36:16.564
Whoa! Whoa!

1039
01:36:16.647 --> 01:36:20.109
<i>Whoa! Whoa!</i>

1040
01:36:20.234 --> 01:36:23.362
Whoa! Whoa!

1041
01:36:35.916 --> 01:36:38.044
Where'd he go?

1042
01:36:38.127 --> 01:36:40.171
Maybe he committed suicide.

1043
01:36:40.296 --> 01:36:42.423
<i>Down here.
you big horse's ass!</i>

1044
01:36:42.506 --> 01:36:45.468
Come and get me
before I call the police!

1045
01:36:45.593 --> 01:36:47.762
- Let's get him!
- Wait. Wait.

1046
01:36:47.845 --> 01:36:49.805
That's just what
he wants us to do--

1047
01:36:49.930 --> 01:36:53.392
us to go back downstairs through
his fun house so we get all tore up.

1048
01:36:53.517 --> 01:36:56.729
- He's gonna call the cops!
- He's not callin' the-- From a tree house?

1049
01:36:56.812 --> 01:36:58.731
Come on.

1050
01:36:58.814 --> 01:37:01.108
- Out the window?
- Yeah.

1051
01:37:01.192 --> 01:37:03.861
- I'm not goin' out the window.
- Why? Are you scared. Marv?

1052
01:37:03.986 --> 01:37:06.572
Are you afraid?
Come on. Get out here.

1053
01:37:11.160 --> 01:37:13.079
Come on.

1054
01:37:16.666 --> 01:37:21.253
<i>Come on!</i>

1055
01:37:25.007 --> 01:37:27.551
Come on.
Keep goin'. Keep goin'.

1056
01:37:27.677 --> 01:37:30.638
- Let's go back. Harry.
- Shut up!

1057
01:37:30.721 --> 01:37:33.975
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

1058
01:37:34.058 --> 01:37:36.894
<i>Shut it. Marv!</i>

1059
01:37:39.355 --> 01:37:42.274
Hey. guys. check this out.

1060
01:37:42.358 --> 01:37:45.152
Go back! Go back!

1061
01:37:45.236 --> 01:37:46.737
- Go back.
- Okay.

1062
01:38:11.012 --> 01:38:15.975
There he goes! There he is!
Get out of the way. you dope!

1063
01:38:33.576 --> 01:38:38.331
- There he is!
- Hey. I'm calling the cops.

1064
01:38:38.414 --> 01:38:41.334
Wait. wait. wait. wait.
He wants us to follow him.

1065
01:38:41.417 --> 01:38:43.544
I got a better idea.
Come on.

1066
01:39:00.478 --> 01:39:04.815
Hiya. pal.
We outsmarted you this time.

1067
01:39:04.940 --> 01:39:07.902
Get over here!

1068
01:39:11.447 --> 01:39:13.449
What are we
gonna do to him. Harry?

1069
01:39:13.574 --> 01:39:17.953
We'll do exactly what he did to us.
I'm gonna burn his head with a blowtorch.

1070
01:39:18.079 --> 01:39:20.206
Then we can smash his face
with an iron!

1071
01:39:20.289 --> 01:39:24.210
<i>I'd like to slap him right in the face
with a paint can maybe.</i>

1072
01:39:24.293 --> 01:39:26.796
<i>Or shove a nail through his foot.</i>

1073
01:39:26.921 --> 01:39:30.174
I'm gonna bite off every one
of these little fingers one at a time.

1074
01:39:38.766 --> 01:39:42.103
Come on.
Let's get you home.

1075
01:40:03.833 --> 01:40:08.004
Wow. This is great.

1076
01:40:10.673 --> 01:40:13.509
Nice move-- always leaving
the water running.

1077
01:40:13.634 --> 01:40:16.846
Now we know each and
every house that you've hit.

1078
01:40:19.807 --> 01:40:23.477
Hey. you know. we've been looking
for you two guys for a long time.

1079
01:40:23.561 --> 01:40:26.522
- Yeah.
- Well. remember. we're the Wet Bandits.

1080
01:40:26.647 --> 01:40:30.776
- Wet Bandits. W-E-T--
- Shut up! Get in the car!

1081
01:40:30.860 --> 01:40:33.696
<i>Hey. come on. Come on.</i>

1082
01:40:33.821 --> 01:40:36.157
- Hands off the head. pal!
- Come on!

1083
01:41:31.879 --> 01:41:34.423
<i>I'm a bad parent.
I'm a bad parent.</i>

1084
01:41:34.548 --> 01:41:37.510
You're not. You know. you're beating
yourself up there. you know.

1085
01:41:37.593 --> 01:41:40.137
Come on. This happens.
These things happen. You know. you--

1086
01:41:40.262 --> 01:41:43.641
Gee. you wanna talk about bad parents?
Look at-- Look at us.

1087
01:41:43.766 --> 01:41:48.187
I mean. we're on the road 48. 49 weeks
out of the year. We hardly see our families.

1088
01:41:48.270 --> 01:41:51.649
Uh. Joe over there-- Gosh. you know. he--

1089
01:41:51.774 --> 01:41:54.485
<i>He forgets his kids' names
half the time.</i>

1090
01:41:54.610 --> 01:41:58.322
<i>Ziggy over there-- He doesn't even--
He's never even met his kid.</i>

1091
01:41:58.447 --> 01:42:02.118
<i>Eddie-- Let's just hope none
of them write a book about him.</i>

1092
01:42:02.243 --> 01:42:07.081
Tell me. have you ever gone on vacation
and left your child home?

1093
01:42:09.959 --> 01:42:12.003
No.

1094
01:42:12.128 --> 01:42:15.548
But I did leave one
at a funeral parlor once.

1095
01:42:15.673 --> 01:42:17.883
Yeah. it was--
it was terrible too.

1096
01:42:17.967 --> 01:42:21.262
You know. I was all distraught and
everything. You know. the wife and I...

1097
01:42:21.387 --> 01:42:25.391
we left the little tyke
there in the funeral parlor all day.

1098
01:42:25.474 --> 01:42:29.395
All day. You know. and we went back
at night when we came to our senses.

1099
01:42:29.478 --> 01:42:32.982
And there he was. Apparently he was
there alone all day with a corpse.

1100
01:42:33.107 --> 01:42:35.735
- Oh!
- Whew. yeah. He was okay. you know.

1101
01:42:35.818 --> 01:42:40.740
After 6. 7 weeks. you know. he
came around and started talking again.

1102
01:42:40.823 --> 01:42:45.286
But he's okay. You know. they get over it.
Kids are resilient like that.

1103
01:42:45.369 --> 01:42:48.122
- Maybe we shouldn't talk about this.
- Well. you brought it up.

1104
01:42:48.205 --> 01:42:51.250
- I was just trying to cheer you up.
- Well. I'm sorry I did.

1105
01:43:17.151 --> 01:43:19.028
Mom?

1106
01:43:23.616 --> 01:43:25.493
Mom?

1107
01:43:28.913 --> 01:43:31.666
Mom?

1108
01:44:17.420 --> 01:44:21.465
Kevin? Kevin!

1109
01:44:52.455 --> 01:44:54.749
Merry Christmas. sweetheart.

1110
01:45:03.966 --> 01:45:06.677
Oh. Kevin. I'm so sorry.

1111
01:45:26.238 --> 01:45:28.366
Where is everybody else?

1112
01:45:28.491 --> 01:45:32.578
Oh. baby. they couldn't come.
They wanted to so much. but--

1113
01:45:32.662 --> 01:45:37.249
I didn't fall asleep in the back of the cab
and drool all over you. did I?

1114
01:45:37.333 --> 01:45:39.627
- I don't drool.
- You guys. would you shut up!

1115
01:45:39.710 --> 01:45:43.047
Come on. you guys. it's Christmas.
Kevin! Kevin. Kevin. my boy!

1116
01:45:43.172 --> 01:45:45.049
- Oh. my God!
- Kevin. how are ya?

1117
01:45:45.174 --> 01:45:47.051
- Merry Christmas.
- Hi. Mom.

1118
01:45:47.176 --> 01:45:49.929
Good to see you. Ah. you're all right.
I love you. You okay?

1119
01:45:50.012 --> 01:45:52.640
- Yeah.
- Hey. Kev.

1120
01:45:54.725 --> 01:45:58.312
It's pretty cool that
you didn't burn the place down.

1121
01:45:58.396 --> 01:46:02.191
<i>Thanks. Buzz.</i>

1122
01:46:02.316 --> 01:46:05.194
<i>Wait a minute.
How did you guys get home?</i>

1123
01:46:05.319 --> 01:46:08.656
Oh. we took the morning flight. Remember?
The one you didn't want to wait for.

1124
01:46:08.739 --> 01:46:11.409
Oh. no.
Oh. thank you.

1125
01:46:11.534 --> 01:46:13.452
<i>- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.</i>

1126
01:46:13.536 --> 01:46:16.093
Someone has to find an open store.
We don't have milk.

1127
01:46:16.119 --> 01:46:17.606
I went shopping yesterday.

1128
01:46:20.001 --> 01:46:21.794
You? Shopping?

1129
01:46:21.877 --> 01:46:24.797
I got some milk. eggs
and fabric softener.

1130
01:46:26.340 --> 01:46:28.676
- What?
- No kiddin'?

1131
01:46:28.801 --> 01:46:32.888
What a funny guy. What else did
you do while we were away?

1132
01:46:33.014 --> 01:46:35.891
Just hung around.

1133
01:46:38.728 --> 01:46:40.855
<i>You guys.
put the stuff upstairs.</i>

1134
01:46:40.980 --> 01:46:44.817
You went shopping? He doesn't know how
to tie his shoe. and he's going shopping?

1135
01:46:44.900 --> 01:46:47.653
<i>- Buzz. forget it.
- This is not the Kevin I knew.</i>

1136
01:47:11.093 --> 01:47:13.429
Honey. what's this?

1137
01:48:11.070 --> 01:48:14.699
<i>Kevin!
What did you do to my room?</i>

1138
01:51:56.023 --> 01:52:00.023
